    <prj:ScienceGoal>
        <prj:name>Imaging the outflow in CZ Vel</prj:name>
        <prj:note>CZ Vel is a semi-detached binary of Algol type, composed of two B type stars, with a period of 5.19d. It shows a strong infrared excess in WISE-4 band (3.669 mag) which is resolved (Chi-squared = 35.4; WISE-4 resolution is 12'').
The full extent of the nebula is about 90'' but we only consider to map the inner (30'') region from which we can retrieve some hints about the ejection mechanism of the nebula. 
</prj:note>
