        <prj:TechnicalJustification>
            <prj:justificationText>We plan to observe in broadband Band 7 (7.5Ghz) with baseband-1 centered on the 12CO (3-2) line at 345.796Ghz to obtain both the black-body continuum of the cold dust seen with WISE as well as molecular line forming in such environment. As there are no radio observations of Algol systems in the spectral range of ALMA so far, we use an extrapolation of the infrared flux F_nu(W4) measured in the WISE W4 band to estimate the flux F_nu(ALMA7) that is to be expected in ALMA's band 7. Although the central engine is different compared to our Algol system, we use observations of AGB stars both in the radio and in the infrared to obtain an idea of the CO emission from dusty environments. For example, Knapp et al. (1997) measured the CO(3-2) emission at 345.796 GHz from the carbon star V Hya. A comparison of their result, after conversion to the ALMA bandwidth, to the flux observed in the WISE W4 band gives the correlation F_nu(ALMA7) = 2.2 F_nu(W4). For CZ Vel (F_nu(W4) = 285 mJy), this gives an expected flux of ~8232 mJy for the total nebula, in band 7 with a 7.5Ghz bandwidth. Since we will resolve the nebula, we estimate the flux per arcsec^2 to be 2.29 mJy/arcsec^2. To obtain a good compromise between SNR and observing time, we set the sensitivity at 100 uJy.</prj:justificationText>
        </prj:TechnicalJustification>
